result.execSummary:
The defendant Hallie M. Frye was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Resisting or Obstructing an Officer, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.41(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes: Referred to Buffalo-Pepin Counties Criminal Justice Coordinating Council for completing 80 hours of community service.  Identify the project by within 30 days. Complete all hours within 7 months.  Failure to complete community service within 7 months will result in the 10 days jail stayed be imposed.
Stayed on condition of completing 80 hours of community service within 7 months.
Costs to be paid in installments of $100.00 per month commencing 10-01-2022 and the first of each month thereafter until paid in full.

records.addlTxt: 1:35 PM Defendant Hallie M. Frye in court with Attorney Melissa M. Petersen by  zoom technology by video.  Attorney Jon D. Seifert appeared by phone for State of Wisconsin.  Agreement reached, PLQ filed.  Will plead to charge, 10 days jail and stayed and do 80 hours community service + court costs.  $443.00.  Court reviews charge/penalties and constitutional rights will be giving up to plead to the charge.  Counsel satisfied factual basis for plea.  Court finds defendant KVI waives constitutional rights and there is a factual basis for plea.  To the charge of obstructing an officer, defendant pleads no contest.  Court accepts your plea and finds you guilty.  Attorney Petersen's sentencing argument and notes no jail credit.  Defendant addresses the court.  Court will order 10 days jail stayed on condition of you doing 80 hours of community service in 7 months.  Identify the project within 30 days.  Contact the C/S Coordinator for approval and report on a monthly basis.  Suggest 12 hours/mo. min.  Court costs of $443.00 TTP $100/mo. com. 10/1/22.  Advised of appeal rights.  Attorney Petersen informs she has filed the notice of postconviction relief form for the record.
